<h3>Definitions</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <h4>Risk Score: </h4>
        Events that will have a negative impact on your project if they occur. Risk refers to the combined likelihood the event will occur and the impact on the project if it does occur. If the likelihood of the event happening and the impact to the project are both high, you identify the event as a serious risk. The log includes a description of each risk, analysis, and a plan to manage it.<br/>
        <img src="~/Img/RiskDef.png" />
    </li>
    <li><h4>Issue Score: </h4>Something that is going wrong on your project and needs to be managed. Failure to manage issues may result in a poor delivery or even failure. The log includes a description of each issue, the impact it is having, its seriousness, and actions needed to contain and remove it.<br/>
        <img src="~/Img/IssueDef.png" />
    </li>
    <li>
        <h4>PM Update Status:</h4>
        If the last PM Update was made within 7 days it is green. If the update was made between 8 or 14 days it is yellow. Any PM update made greater than 14 days ago is red.
    </li>
    <li>
        <h4>Milestones</h4>
        If the project is missing 0 milestones it is green. If the project is mising 1 milestone it is yellow. If the project is missing more than 1 milestone it is red. The missing milestones can be seen by hovering over the traffic light color.
    </li>
    <li>
        <h4>Staffing</h4>
        If the project has 0 unstaffed projects of if the closest unstaffed task is 8 weeks out then it is green. If the project has an unstaffed task within 8 weeks from today it is yellow. If the project has no workplan or an unstaffed task occurs today or in the past it is red.
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>FAQ</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <h4>How do I copy the tooltip text?</h4>
        You can copy the tooltip text by clicking the cell that contains the tooltip text you would like to copy. Doing so will open a new window with the text on the webpage for you to copy.
    </li>
</ul>
